%N A387830 Least number of vertical or horizontal cuts required to divide a square into n equal parts.
%C A387830 Each cut is required to go pass all the way through the square.
%C A387830 Equivalently, a(n) is the minimum of (d-1) + (n/d-1) over all divisors d of n.
%F A387830 a(p) = p - 1 for p prime.
%F A387830 a(n) = Min_{d|n} d + n/d - 2. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Oct 07 2025
%F A387830 a(n) = A063655(n) - 2. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 07 2025
%e A387830 a(6) = 3 since a square can be divided into 6 equal parts using 3 cuts (2 vertical and 1 horizontal).
%t A387830 a[n_]:= Min[Table[d + n/d - 2,{d,Divisors[n]}]]; Array[a,70] (* _Stefano Spezia_, Oct 09 2025 *)
%o A387830 (PARI) a(n) = {my(m=n+1); fordiv(n, d, m=min(m, d+n/d)); m-2} \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Oct 07 2025
